    <main>
      <h2>Cluster Bomb</h2>
      <p>From a cop's raised gun<br>
	Through the head of the boy<br>
	Of sixteen years, standing alone<br>
	On that grassy knoll.<br>
      </p>

      <p>The lead pellets<br>
	wrapped in a bean bag<br>
	slice the still air and<br>
	smash into his skull
      </p>

      <p>Crippling his young mind<br>
	Too young to know<br>
	Those holes left in the towers<br>
	Twenty years ago.
      </p>

      <p>That was the age<br>
	Of another young man<br>
	Shot in the head by the<br>
	Police, with their little lead balls, that
      </p>

      <p>Like cluster bombs<br>
	Dropped from afar<br>
	Spread deadly pain<br>
	to all those around.
      </p>
      
